<inglise> COMMISSION DECISION No 3010/91/ECSC of 15 October 1991 on the information to be furnished by steel undertakings about their investments </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI OTSUS nr 3010/91/EST&Uuml; teabe kohta, mida teraseettev&otilde;tted peavad oma investeeringute kohta esitama 15. oktoober 1991 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the Coal and Steel Community, and in particular Article 54 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa S&ouml;e- ja Terase&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 54, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 54 of the Treaty entrusts the High Authority with the task of encouraging coordinated development of investment; whereas it must therefore be able to form an opinion, within the framework of the general objectives set out in Article 46, on the investment and disinvestment programmes of undertakings; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: asutamislepingu artikliga 54 tehakse &uuml;lemametile &uuml;lesandeks edendada investeeringute koosk&otilde;lastatud arengut; seep&auml;rast peab &uuml;lemametil olema v&otilde;imalik v&otilde;tta seisukoht investeerimisprogrammide ja negatiivsete investeeringute programmide suhtes artiklis 46 s&auml;testatud &uuml;ldeesm&auml;rkide raames; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas investment and permanent disinvestment programmes must at present be notified in accordance with Commission Decision No 3302/81/ECSC (1), as amended by Decision No 2093/85/ECSC (2); </inglise>
<eesti> investeerimisprogrammidest ja negatiivsete investeeringute programmidest tuleb praegu teatada vastavalt komisjoni otsusele nr 3302/81/EST&Uuml;, (1) muudetud otsusega nr 2093/85/EST&Uuml; (2); </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the special difficulties with which the steel industry has recently been faced and as a consequence of which a state of manifest crisis was declared, after which the mandatory measures provided for in the ECSC Treaty for the organization of the steel market were introduced, together with a system for supervising public aid to this sector, have disappeared, and consequently the special emphasis placed on very detailed monitoring of the investment and disinvestment activity of undertakings can now be relaxed; </inglise>
<eesti> teraset&ouml;&ouml;stuses viimasel ajal esinenud raskused, mille tagaj&auml;rjel kuulutati v&auml;lja ilmne kriisiolukord, mille j&auml;rel kehtestati EST&Uuml; asutamislepinguga etten&auml;htud kohustuslikud meetmed teraseturu korralduse kohta ja loodi sellele valdkonnale antava avaliku abi j&auml;relevalve s&uuml;steem, on kadunud ja seega v&otilde;ib ettev&otilde;tete investeerimistegevuse ja negatiivse investeerimistegevuse j&auml;relevalvele pandud erilist r&otilde;hku n&uuml;&uuml;d leevendada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to carry out the task entrusted to it by Article 54 of the Treaty, the Commission must, however, continue to have detailed knowledge of the steel production plant in operation, under construction or planned, the investment activity and the extension of production capacities in the sector, with regular updating of such information; </inglise>
<eesti> selleks et t&auml;ita talle asutamislepingu artikliga 54 usaldatud &uuml;lesannet, peavad komisjonil siiski j&auml;tkuvalt olema t&auml;psed andmed t&ouml;&ouml;tavatest, ehitatavatest v&otilde;i kavandatavatest terasetootmisettev&otilde;tetest, investeerimistegevusest ja tootmisv&otilde;imsuse laiendamisest selles valdkonnas, ja seda teavet tuleb korrap&auml;raselt ajakohastada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it must also be specifically informed in detail of, on the one hand, investment projects on a scale likely to have a significant effect on the balance between supply and demand and, on the other, permanent closures of major production plant; </inglise>
<eesti> samuti peab komisjoni teavitama &uuml;ksikasjalikult investeerimisprojektidest, mille ulatus m&otilde;jutab t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt m&auml;rgatavalt pakkumise ja n&otilde;udluse vahelist tasakaalu, ja suuremate tootmisettev&otilde;tete l&otilde;plikust sulgemisest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this Decision replaces the existing rules governing the information to be furnished by iron and steel undertakings about their investments and disinvestments, with the result that Decision No 3302/81/ECSC now needs to be repealed, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolev otsus asendab olemasolevaid eeskirju, mis reguleerivad malmi- ja teraset&ouml;&ouml;stuse ettev&otilde;tete poolt nende investeeringuid ja negatiivseid investeeringuid k&auml;sitleva teabe esitamist, ja seep&auml;rast tuleb otsus nr 3302/81/EST&Uuml; tunnistada kehtetuks, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DECISION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION I </inglise>
<eesti> I JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> Prior notification of investment programmes for production plant </inglise>
<eesti> Tootmisettev&otilde;tete investeerimisprogrammidega seotud eelnev teatamine </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision shall relate exclusively to investment for activities in the iron and steel industry. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus on seotud &uuml;ksnes malmi- ja teraset&ouml;&ouml;stuse investeeringutega. </eesti>
<inglise> Investment for coalmining activities shall remain subject to the provisions of Decision No 22-66 (3), as amended by Decision No 2237/73/ECSC (4) as long as no new decision on this sector has been adopted. </inglise>
<eesti> S&ouml;ekaevandamisega seotud investeeringute suhtes kohaldatakse j&auml;tkuvalt otsuse nr 22/66 (3) (muudetud otsusega nr 2237/73/EST&Uuml; (4)) s&auml;tteid, kuni v&otilde;etakse vastu k&auml;esoleva valdkonnaga seotud uus otsus. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> All Community steel undertakings engaged in production within the meaning of Article 80 of the ECSC Treaty shall notify the Commission of any investment programmes relating to their production activities in respect of one or more of the products listed in Annex I to the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;ik &uuml;henduse teraseettev&otilde;tted, mis on seotud tootmisega EST&Uuml; asutamislepingu artikli 80 t&auml;henduses, teatavad komisjonile k&otilde;ikidest investeerimisprogrammidest, mis on seotud nende tootmistegevusega &uuml;he v&otilde;i enama asutamislepingu I lisas loetletud toote osas. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Prior notification shall cover investment programmes relating to new or existing plant the estimated cost of which exceeds ECU 25 million or which will increase production capacity for the products listed in Annex I to the ECSC Treaty by more than 50 000 tonnes per year. </inglise>
<eesti> Eelnev teatamine peab h&otilde;lmama investeerimisprogramme, mis on seotud uue v&otilde;i olemasoleva tootmisettev&otilde;ttega, mille hinnangkulud on &uuml;le 25 miljoni ek&uuml;&uuml; v&otilde;i mis suurendavad tootmismahtu EST&Uuml; asutamislepingu I lisas loetletud toodete osas rohkem kui 50 000 tonni aastas. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to evaluate the total estimated cost and the increase in production capacity referred to in the preceding paragraph, all the elements constituting a technically indivisible whole should be combined in a single programme, even if their implementation covers several distinct stages in time. </inglise>
<eesti> Hinnanguliste kogukulude ja eelmises l&otilde;igus osutatud tootmismahu kasvu hindamiseks tuleks k&otilde;ik elemendid, mis moodustavad tehniliselt lahutamatu terviku, koondada &uuml;hte programmi, isegi kui nende rakendamine koosneks mitmest ajaliselt erinevast etapist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Notifications shall cover: </inglise>
<eesti> Teatised h&otilde;lmavad j&auml;rgmist: </eesti>
<inglise> - a description of the position occupied by the investment programme in the development strategy of the undertaking and the decision-making centre, </inglise>
<eesti> - investeerimisprogrammi positsioon ettev&otilde;tte ja otsuste tegemise keskuse arengustrateegias, </eesti>
<inglise> - an exact description of the investment programme and its foreseeable impact on the environment, </inglise>
<eesti> - investeerimisprogrammi t&auml;pne kirjeldus ja selle eeldatav m&otilde;ju keskkonnale, </eesti>
<inglise> - the maximum technical capacity of the plant concerned, </inglise>
<eesti> - asjaomase tootmisettev&otilde;tte maksimaalne tehniline v&otilde;imsus, </eesti>
<inglise> - any compensating closures of other plant, </inglise>
<eesti> - muude tootmisettev&otilde;tete tasakaalustav sulgemine, </eesti>
<inglise> - the effect which the investment programme will have on the production potential for the product or products in question, in relation to the works, the undertaking and the decision-making centre concerned, </inglise>
<eesti> - investeerimisprogrammi m&otilde;ju k&otilde;nealuse toote v&otilde;i k&otilde;nealuste toodete tootmisv&otilde;imsusele tehase, ettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i asjaomase otsuste tegemise keskuse tasandil, </eesti>
<inglise> - the approximate amount of forecast expenditure, broken down where appropriate into material investments and invisible expenditure, e.g. interim interest, </inglise>
<eesti> - ligikaudsed eeldatavad kulud, mis jaotatakse vajaduse korral materiaalseteks investeeringuteks ja n&auml;htamatuteks kuludeks, n&auml;iteks vaheintress, </eesti>
<inglise> - the exact timetable: start of work (month and year) and duration (in months), </inglise>
<eesti> - t&auml;pne ajakava, t&ouml;&ouml;de algus (kuu ja aasta) ja kestus (kuudes), </eesti>
<inglise> - the number of jobs created or lost, and the number of persons affected, </inglise>
<eesti> - loodud v&otilde;i kaotatud t&ouml;&ouml;kohtade arv ning nende isikute arv, keda see m&otilde;jutab, </eesti>
<inglise> - any effect on the supply of raw materials, </inglise>
<eesti> - v&otilde;imalik m&otilde;ju toorainetega varustamisele, </eesti>
<inglise> - profitability calculations in respect of the amounts invested, giving the main factors and the result of the calculations, e.g. internal rate of return or pay-back period, except where this calculation was not involved in the decision-making process of the undertaking, in which case it shall state the reasons why account was not taken of this factor, </inglise>
<eesti> - investeeritud summade tasuvusarvutus, milles esitatakse peamised tegurid ja arvutuse tulemus, n&auml;iteks sisemine tasuvusl&auml;vi v&otilde;i tasuvusaeg, kui see arvutus ei kuulunud ettev&otilde;tte otsustamisprotsessi - sel juhul tuleb p&otilde;hjendada, miks seda tegurit arvesse ei v&otilde;etud, </eesti>
<inglise> - the sources of funding to be used for implementing the investment programme. </inglise>
<eesti> - investeerimisprogrammi rakendamisel kasutatavad rahastamisallikad. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Notifications concerning investment programmes must be sent to the Commission as soon as possible after the decision has been taken by the undertaking, and not later than three months before the first contracts are concluded with the suppliers or, if the work is to be carried out by the undertaking itself, three months before the work is put in hand. </inglise>
<eesti> Investeerimisprogrammidega seotud teatised tuleb saata komisjonile niipea kui v&otilde;imalik p&auml;rast ettev&otilde;tte otsuse tegemist ja hiljemalt kolm kuud enne esimeste tarnelepingute s&otilde;lmimist v&otilde;i kui ettev&otilde;te kavatseb teha t&ouml;&ouml; oma ressurssidega, siis kolm kuud enne t&ouml;&ouml;de algust. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Information in respect of any major changes in investment programmes notified to the Commission shall be forwarded in an amending notification in the form and within the time limits laid down in Articles 4 and 5. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjonile teatatud investeerimisprogrammides tehtud suurte muudatuste kohta tuleb esitada parandusteatis artiklites 4 ja 5 s&auml;testatud vormis ja t&auml;htaja jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise> Decisions shall be considered as involving major changes if they are liable to delay the start or the implementation of the programme by at least one year, to double its estimated cost or reduce it by half, or to increase or decrease estimated production capacity by at least 50 000 tonnes per year. </inglise>
<eesti> Otsused sisaldavad suuri muudatusi, kui need l&uuml;kkaksid edasi programmi alguse v&otilde;i rakendamise v&auml;hemalt &uuml;he aasta v&otilde;rra, kahekordistaksid hinnangkulusid v&otilde;i v&auml;hendaksid neid poole v&otilde;rra v&otilde;i suurendaksid v&otilde;i v&auml;hendaksid eeldatavat tootmisv&otilde;imsust v&auml;hemalt 50 000 tonni v&otilde;rra aastas. </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION II </inglise>
<eesti> II JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> Prior notification of the permanent closure of production plant </inglise>
<eesti> Tootmisettev&otilde;tte l&otilde;pliku sulgemisega seotud eelnev teatamine </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Every steel undertaking within the Community shall notify the Commission of permanent closures of plant affecting one or more of the products listed in Annex I to the ECSC Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;ik &uuml;henduse teraseettev&otilde;tted teatavad komisjonile tootmisettev&otilde;tte l&otilde;plikust sulgemisest, mis m&otilde;jutab &uuml;hte v&otilde;i enamat EST&Uuml; asutamislepingu I lisas loetletud toodet. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> Notification shall cover any permanent closure, transfer or sale of complete plant, i.e. whole production units (coke oven battery, blast furnace, LD converter, electric arc furnace, etc). </inglise>
<eesti> Teatis h&otilde;lmab tervet tootmisettev&otilde;tet, see t&auml;hendab kogu tootmis&uuml;ksuse (koksiahi, k&otilde;rgahi, hapnikkonverter, elektrikaarahi jne) l&otilde;plikku sulgemist, v&otilde;&otilde;randamist v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;ki. </eesti>
<inglise> The only closures considered to be permanent shall be those where the key elements listed in the fourth paragraph of this Article must be physically destroyed so that the plant cannot be restored to service, of if the plant is to be sold or transferred. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;pliku sulgemisena k&auml;sitletakse sulgemist, mille puhul k&auml;esoleva artikli neljandas l&otilde;igus loetletud p&otilde;hielemendid h&auml;vitatakse f&uuml;&uuml;siliselt, nii et ettev&otilde;tet ei oleks v&otilde;imalik taastada, v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;te m&uuml;&uuml;akse v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randatakse. </eesti>
<inglise> Notification of permanent closures shall imply a decision on the part of the undertaking to destroy the key elements of the plant concerned, or to sell or transfer the plant within six months of the date on which production ceases. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;pliku sulgemise teatis peab sisaldama ettev&otilde;tte otsust asjaomase tootmisettev&otilde;tte p&otilde;hielementide h&auml;vitamise kohta v&otilde;i tootmisettev&otilde;tte m&uuml;&uuml;gi v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randamise kohta kuue kuu jooksul p&auml;rast tootmise l&otilde;petamise kuup&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise> Before a closure can be deemed permanent, the following key elements must be destroyed: </inglise>
<eesti> Sulgemist saab k&auml;sitleda l&otilde;plikuna, kui j&auml;rgmised p&otilde;hielemendid on h&auml;vitatud: </eesti>
<inglise> - in the case of hot rolling mills: reheating furnaces, rolling mill stands and cooling beds, </inglise>
<eesti> - kuumvaltspinkide puhul: kuumutusahjud, valtsraamid ja jahutusalused, </eesti>
<inglise> - in the case of cold rolling mills: mill stands, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&uuml;lmvaltspinkide puhul: valtsraamid, </eesti>
<inglise> - in the case of coating plant: coiling machines, accumulators, and tanks or cells used to apply the coating, </inglise>
<eesti> - pindamisseadme puhul: pealekerimisseadmed, akumulaatorid ning pindamisel kasutatavad mahutid, </eesti>
<inglise> - in the case of other plant: components whose destruction makes it impossible to operate the plant: e.g. the tilting mechanism of LD converters; the steel jacket, superstructures and, where appropriate, the square tower of a blast furnace; the pushing machine in a coking plant. </inglise>
<eesti> - muude seadmete puhul: elemendid, mille h&auml;vitamise t&otilde;ttu ei ole seadet v&otilde;imalik k&auml;itada: n&auml;iteks hapnikkonverteri kallutusmehhanism; k&otilde;rgahju teraskest, pealisehitised ja vajaduse korral k&otilde;rgahju nelikantsuue; koksiahju t&otilde;ukurseade. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission reserves the right to make site inspections to verify the removal or destruction of the key elements defined in the fourth paragraph of this Article. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon j&auml;tab endale &otilde;iguse kontrollida kohapeal k&auml;esoleva artikli neljandas l&otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;ratletud p&otilde;hielementide k&otilde;rvaldamist v&otilde;i h&auml;vitamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> Notification shall cover: </inglise>
<eesti> Teatis h&otilde;lmab j&auml;rgmist: </eesti>
<inglise> - the reasons which led to the closure decision, </inglise>
<eesti> - p&otilde;hjused, mille tagaj&auml;rjel tehti sulgemisotsus, </eesti>
<inglise> - an exact description of the plant to be withdrawn from service, </inglise>
<eesti> - tegevust l&otilde;petava tootmisettev&otilde;tte t&auml;pne kirjeldus, </eesti>
<inglise> - exact details of the immediate future of the plant (demolition, sale, transfer), </inglise>
<eesti> - t&auml;psed &uuml;ksikasjad tootmisettev&otilde;tte l&auml;hituleviku kohta (lammutamine, m&uuml;&uuml;k, v&otilde;&otilde;randamine), </eesti>
<inglise> - the date on which the proposed measures will be completed, </inglise>
<eesti> - kavandatavate meetmete t&auml;itmise kuup&auml;ev, </eesti>
<inglise> - actual production during the 12 months preceding notification, </inglise>
<eesti> - teatisele eelneva 12 kuu tegelik toodang, </eesti>
<inglise> - the results expected, especially as regards production and production capacity, for the works, the undertaking and the decision-making centre, </inglise>
<eesti> - eeldatavad tulemused, eelk&otilde;ige tehase, ettev&otilde;tte ja otsuste tegemise keskuse tootmise ja tootmisv&otilde;imsusega seotud tulemused, </eesti>
<inglise> - the effects on the workforce (number of jobs lost and number of persons affected) and the possibilities, if any, of re-employing the workforce affected by the closure, </inglise>
<eesti> - m&otilde;ju t&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;ule (kaotatud t&ouml;&ouml;kohtade ja sellest m&otilde;jutatud isikute arv) ja v&otilde;imalused v&otilde;tta uuesti t&ouml;&ouml;le t&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;ud, keda sulgemine on m&otilde;jutanud, </eesti>
<inglise> - in the case of sale or transfer, the name of the undertaking to which the plant is to be sold or transferred. </inglise>
<eesti> - m&uuml;&uuml;gi v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randamise korral ettev&otilde;tte nimi, kellele tootmisettev&otilde;te m&uuml;&uuml;akse v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randatakse. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> Notifications concerning permanent closures shall be sent to the Commission as soon as possible after the decision has been taken by the undertaking, and not later than one month before the event which will mark the end of the plant's operation (beginning of demolition work, date on which the contract of sale takes effect, closure, etc.). </inglise>
<eesti> Tootmisettev&otilde;tte l&otilde;pliku sulgemisega seotud teatised tuleb saata komisjonile niipea kui v&otilde;imalik p&auml;rast ettev&otilde;tte otsuse tegemist ja hiljemalt &uuml;ks kuu enne tootmisettev&otilde;tte tegevuse l&otilde;petamist (lammutamise algus, m&uuml;&uuml;gilepingu j&otilde;ustumise kuup&auml;ev, sulgemine jne). </eesti>
<inglise> Article 11 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 11 </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission must be informed by means of an amending notification of any changes made to such notified permanent closure programmes as soon as possible after the relevant decision by the undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjonile peab parandusteatise abil teatama k&otilde;ikidest l&otilde;pliku sulgemise programmidesse tehtud muudatustest niipea kui v&otilde;imalik p&auml;rast seda, kui ettev&otilde;tte on teinud asjakohase otsuse. </eesti>
<inglise> Any decision cancelling the closure or likely either to bring it forward or to postpone it by at least a year shall, in particular, be regarded as involving major changes. </inglise>
<eesti> Mis tahes otsust, millega sulgemine t&uuml;histatakse v&otilde;i v&auml;hemalt aasta v&otilde;rra ettepoole tuuakse v&otilde;i edasi l&uuml;katakse, k&auml;sitletakse olulise muudatusena. </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION III </inglise>
<eesti> III JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> Reports on the implementation of programmes of investment or permanent closure of production plant </inglise>
<eesti> Aruanded investeerimisprogrammide rakendamise ja tootmisettev&otilde;tte l&otilde;pliku sulgemise kohta </eesti>
<inglise> Article 12 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 12 </eesti>
<inglise> All Community steel undertakings shall send to the Commission a report on the actual manner of implementation of the programmes of investment or permanent closure of production plant referred to in Sections I and II and of any other investment programmes of which the actual cost has, contrary to estimates, exceeded the limits given in Article 3. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;ik &uuml;henduse teraseettev&otilde;tted saadavad komisjonile aruande investeerimisprogrammide, k&auml;esoleva otsuse I ja II jaos osutatud tootmisettev&otilde;tte l&otilde;pliku sulgemise programmide v&otilde;i mis tahes muude investeerimisprogrammide, mille tegelik kulu on vastupidiselt hinnangutele &uuml;letanud artiklis 3 esitatud piirm&auml;&auml;rad, tegeliku rakendamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 13 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 13 </eesti>
<inglise> Reports shall contain: </inglise>
<eesti> Aruanded peavad sisaldama j&auml;rgmist: </eesti>
<inglise> - an exact description of the programme of investment or permanent closure carried out, with specific reference to any changes made to the original programme; in the case of sale or transfer of a permanently closed plant, the name of the undertaking to which it is to be sold or transferred, </inglise>
<eesti> - teostatud investeerimis- v&otilde;i l&otilde;pliku sulgemise programmide t&auml;pne kirjeldus koos viitega originaalprogrammis tehtud muudatustele; l&otilde;plikult suletud tootmisettev&otilde;tte m&uuml;&uuml;gi v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randamise korral ettev&otilde;tte nimi, kellele see m&uuml;&uuml;akse v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randatakse, </eesti>
<inglise> - the date of completion of the programme of investment or permanent closure (if the programme was carried out in a number of stages, the date of completion of these stages), </inglise>
<eesti> - investeerimis- v&otilde;i l&otilde;pliku sulgemise programmi l&otilde;puleviimise kuup&auml;ev (kui programm viidi ellu mitmes etapis, nende etappide l&otilde;puleviimise kuup&auml;ev), </eesti>
<inglise> - the expenditure incurred, </inglise>
<eesti> - tehtud kulutused, </eesti>
<inglise> - all information on: </inglise>
<eesti> - kogu teave, mis on seotud: </eesti>
<inglise> - the purpose and technical nature of the work carried out, </inglise>
<eesti> - tehtud t&ouml;&ouml; eesm&auml;rgi ja tehnilise laadiga, </eesti>
<inglise> - the results already obtained or expected as a result of the implementation of the programme, particularly as regards production and production capacity, with specific mention of any divergence from the originally expected results, </inglise>
<eesti> - programmi rakendamisel saadud v&otilde;i eeldatavate tulemustega, eelk&otilde;ige tootmise ja tootmisv&otilde;imsuse suhtes, mille puhul on mainitud v&otilde;imalikud k&otilde;rvalekalded esialgselt eeldatud tulemustest, </eesti>
<inglise> - the supply of raw materials, </inglise>
<eesti> - toorainete tarnimisega, </eesti>
<inglise> - the effects on the workforce, </inglise>
<eesti> - m&otilde;juga t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivele, </eesti>
<inglise> - the sources of finance for the investment programme. </inglise>
<eesti> - investeerimisprogrammi rahastamisallikatega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 14 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 14 </eesti>
<inglise> The reports referred to in Article 12 must be sent to the Commission as soon as possible and not later than three months after the plant to which they refer starts or ceases to operate. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 12 osutatud aruanded tuleb saata komisjonile niipea kui v&otilde;imalik ja hiljemalt kolm kuud p&auml;rast seda, kui osutatud tootmisettev&otilde;te alustab tegevust v&otilde;i l&otilde;petab oma tegevuse. </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION IV </inglise>
<eesti> IV JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> Periodic surveys </inglise>
<eesti> Perioodilised vaatlused </eesti>
<inglise> Article 15 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 15 </eesti>
<inglise> In addition to the notifications and reports referred to above, all Community steel undertakings shall reply to the Commission's periodic surveys, particularly those concerning plant and investment and its effect on production capacity. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaks eespool osutatud teatistele ja aruannetele peavad k&otilde;ik &uuml;henduse teraseettev&otilde;tted vastama komisjoni perioodilistele vaatlustele, eriti neile, mis on seotud uute tootmisettev&otilde;tete ja investeeringutega ning nende m&otilde;juga tootmisv&otilde;imsusele. </eesti>
<inglise> Replies to the periodic surveys shall include all plant not permanently closed within the meaning of Article 8. </inglise>
<eesti> Perioodilistele vaatlustele peavad vastama k&otilde;ik tootmisettev&otilde;tted, mida ei ole artikli 8 t&auml;henduses l&otilde;plikult suletud. </eesti>
<inglise> A summary of the results of these surveys shall be published and sent to those concerned, in conformity with the second paragraph of Article 47 of the ECSC Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> Nende vaatluste tulemuste kokkuv&otilde;te avaldatakse ja saadetakse asjaomastele isikutele vastavalt EST&Uuml; asutamislepingu artikli 47 teisele l&otilde;igule. </eesti>
<inglise> Replies to the investment survey must, in particular, contain details of all changes in capacity, even those still at the planning stage. </inglise>
<eesti> Investeerimisvaatluse vastused peavad eelk&otilde;ige sisaldama k&otilde;iki tootmisv&otilde;imsusega seotud muudatusi, sealhulgas ka kavandatavaid. </eesti>
<inglise> Such replies shall not exempt undertakings from submitting, in due course, a notification in accordance with Sections I and II. </inglise>
<eesti> Need vastused ei vabasta ettev&otilde;tteid kohustusest esitada &otilde;igeaegselt I ja II jaoga koosk&otilde;las olevat teatist. </eesti>
<inglise> SECTION V </inglise>
<eesti> V JAGU </eesti>
<inglise> General provisions </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise> Article 16 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 16 </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall acknowledge receipt of investment and closure notifications and of reports which are sent to it, and may request any additional information it considers necessary. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon teatab investeerimis- ja sulgemisteatiste ning talle saadetud aruannete k&auml;ttesaamisest ja v&otilde;ib taotleda sellise lisateabe esitamist, mida ta peab vajalikuks. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission reserves the right to deliver a reasoned opinion, as provided for in the fourth paragraph of Article 54 of the ECSC Treaty, on the notified investment programmes. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon j&auml;tab endale &otilde;iguse esitada EST&Uuml; asutamislepingu artikli 54 neljandas l&otilde;igus s&auml;testatud p&otilde;hjendatud arvamus teatatud investeerimisprogrammide kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> If the Commission intends to deliver such an opinion unde the general objectives provided for in Article 46 of the ECSC Treaty, it shall inform the undertaking within three months of the date on which the confirmation of receipt of the notification is sent. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui komisjon kavatseb esitada sellise arvamuse EST&Uuml; asutamislepingu artiklis 46 s&auml;testatud &uuml;ldeesm&auml;rkide alusel, teatab ta sellest ettev&otilde;ttele kolme kuu jooksul alates kuup&auml;evast, millal teatise saamise kinnitus saadetakse. </eesti>
<inglise> If the undertaking expressly requests it, the Commission shall deliver such an opinion in all cases. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui ettev&otilde;te seda otseselt taotleb, esitab komisjon selle arvamuse k&otilde;ikidel juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise> Undertakings which evade their obligations under this Decision or furnish false information shall be liable to the fines and penalties provided for under Article 47 of the ECSC Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> Ettev&otilde;tete suhtes, kes hoiavad k&otilde;rvale neile k&auml;esoleva otsuse alusel pandud kohustuste t&auml;itmisest v&otilde;i esitavad valeandmeid, v&otilde;ib kohaldada EST&Uuml; asutamislepingu artiklis 47 s&auml;testatud trahve ja karistusi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 17 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 17 </eesti>
<inglise> Investment and closure notifications, reports and replies to the periodic surveys referred to in Article 15 must be sent to the following department of the Commission of the European Communities: Directorate-General XVIII, </inglise>
<eesti> Investeerimis- ja sulgemisteatised, aruanded ja artiklis 15 osutatud perioodiliste vaatluste vastused tuleb saata j&auml;rgmisele Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Komisjoni osakonnale: </eesti>
<inglise> Unit'Opinions on investments and enquiries', B&acirc;timent Wagner, </inglise>
<eesti> Directorate-General XVIII, Unit 'Opinions on investments and enquiries', B&acirc;timent Wagner, L-2920 Luxembourg. </eesti>
